Structure for Docker:
whisper_large_v3/
├── audio/                    # ← Put your audio files here
│   └── (your audio files)
├── output/                   # ← Transcripts will appear here
├── config-docker.json        # Docker-specific config
├── config.json              # Local dev config (optional)
├── Dockerfile
├── docker-compose.yml
├── requirements.txt
├── main.py
├── config.py
├── input_output_manager.py
├── statistics_report.py
└── text_formatter.py

How to use:
1. Build the image:
# Navigate to project root
cd E:\A\ai\whisper_large_v3

# Delete Docker image if it needs
docker rmi whisper-v3:latest

# check the containers that are running
docker ps -a

# Stop container if it needs
docker stop container-name

# Delete container if it needs
docker rm container-id

# Build Docker image
docker build -t whisper-v3 .

# check image
docker images
docker images whisper-v3  # if name is known

# Run docker
docker run --rm --user root -v "your full path to whisper_large_v3\config.json:/app/config.json" -v "your full path to GPTforJava\src\main\resources\ch04\target_TheOnePlaceICantGo:/app/audio" whisper-v3

# run app locally
python main.py --config ..\..\config-local.json

# Run Docker Compose project and substitute all the variables from the custom.env file.
docker compose --env-file custom.env up
docker compose --env-file custom.env up --build


